The paper discusses pretraining deep reinforcement learning algorithms with expert demonstrations, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The paper focuses on actor-critic reinforcement learning algorithms, which are commonly used in robotics and control applications, suggesting that the paper may belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. However, the paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks, which suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper applies the proposed method to two reinforcement learning algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Overall, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
